  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Sales Director",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Technical Sales Director</strong></u></p>\n<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li> <strong>Strategic Sales Leadership:</strong> Own the full sales cycle for a defined territory or set of strategic accounts, from prospecting and qualification to negotiation and closure.</li>\n  <li><strong>Technical Solutioning:</strong> Conduct deep-dive discovery sessions and product demonstrations, translating complex technical features into compelling business outcomes for C-level executives and technical stakeholders.</li>\n  <li><strong>Relationship Building:</strong> Cultivate strong, trusted-advisor relationships with key decision-makers (CEO, CFO, CTO).</li>\n  <li><strong>Team Mentorship:</strong> Provide guidance, mentorship, and technical sales support to a team of Account Executives and Business Development Representatives.</li>\n  <li><strong>Market Intelligence:</strong> Serve as the \"voice of the customer,\" feeding critical insights from the field back to our Product, Engineering, and Marketing teams to inform our go-to-market strategy.</li>\n  <li><strong>Quarterly &amp; Annual Targets:</strong> Be accountable for achieving and exceeding significant sales quotas and revenue targets.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Who You Are</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li> A strategic hunter who thrives on identifying and landing seven-figure, complex enterprise deals.</li>\n  <li>A compelling storyteller who can articulate a powerful vision to both technical and business audiences.</li>\n  <li>A problem-solver at heart, with the ability to architect sophisticated solutions to challenging customer problems.</li>\n  <li>A collaborative leader who enjoys winning as a team and elevating those around you.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>8+ years of B2B sales experience in local and overseas MRO (Maintenance, Repair and Overhaul) industry, of which Minimum 5 years’ experience in the Marine industry</li>\n  <li>Proven track record of selling and completion projection execution in complex composite repair and high-value technical solutions</li>\n  <li>3+ years in a sales leadership or team lead role, with experience mentoring and enabling other sales professionals.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrable experience consistently exceeding multi-million dollar revenue targets.</li>\n  <li>Deep technical proficiency with ASME (American Standard of Mechanical Engineers) Standards and Compliance.</li>\n  <li>Exceptional presentation, negotiation, and executive-facing communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Minimum Bachelor's Degree preferably in Mechanical or      Chemical Engineering</li>\n  <li>Able to handle stress and meet tight deadlines</li>\n  <li>Singaporeans &amp; Spore PRs only</li>\n</ul>",
